05017nam a22007575i 9783110926170DE-B159720211217065530.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211217t20112003gw     fo  d z      ger d  a97831109261707 a10.1515/97831109261702doi  a(DE-B1597)46919  a(OCoLC)979590325  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 ager  agwcDE 4aDS115b.I58 2001 7aLIT0000002bisacsh04a920.0092/92422300aZeitgenössische jüdische Autobiographie /chrsg. von Christoph Miething.  aReprint 2011 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2011] 4c©2003  a1 online resource (199 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aRomania Judaica : Studien zur jüdischen Kultur in den romanischen Ländern ,x1435-098X ;v70 aOpen Accessuhttps://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_abf2funrestricted online access2star  aDie Akten des gleichnamigen Kongresses vereinigen Beiträge vor allem zur französisch-jüdischen Autobiographie der letzten Jahrzehnte. Aber auch die einschlägige deutsch- und englischsprachige Literatur wird berücksichtigt. Drei italienische Autoren von Autobiographien kommen ebenfalls zu Wort und nehmen zu ihrem Werk Stellung. Die theoretische Reflexion, die die Analyse einzelner Werke begleitet oder auch selbständig durchgeführt wird, betrifft einerseits das Verhältnis von Autobiographie und 'Autofiktion', und andererseits die grundsätzliche Frage, was es heißt, von 'jüdischen Autobiographien' zu reden.  aThe proceedings of the conference of the same name assemble papers concentrating largely on Franco-Jewish autobiography in the last few decades. Relevant literature in English and German is also discussed. In addition, three Italian authors of autobiographies comment on their own works. The theoretical reflection undertaken in the volume either accompanies the analysis of individual works or takes a broader view. It centres (a) on the relationship between autobiography and 'auto-fiction', and (b) on the fundamental issue of what we precisely mean when we speak of 'Jewish autobiographies'.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aAutobiographyxJewish authorsvCongresses. 0aJewsvBiographyvCongresses. 4aAutobiographie. 4aJuden. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aChiantaretto, Jean-François, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFubini, Guido, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHilfrich, Carola, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLecarme, Jacques, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLezzi, Eva, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLoewe, Siegfried, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiething, Christoph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiething, Christoph, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMingelgrün, Albert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMolkou, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNolden, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPinto, Diana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSacerdoti, Paola, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeissberg, Liliane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZargani, Aldo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR0 cprintz978348457007840uhtt